section.section:
"Approved source" includes:
An artesian well;
A drilled well;
A glacier;
A public water supply;
A spring; and
A source of mineral water that complies with the standards specified in paragraph (1) of this subsection but fails to meet the standards with respect to those properties of mineral water related to the limitations on chloride, iron, manganese, sulfate, total dissolved solids, zinc, or any other exemptions listed under 21 C.F.R. 165.110.

The Advisory Committee shall consist of the following representatives:
The Secretary of Health and Mental Hygiene or the Secretary's designee, who shall serve as chairman of the Advisory Committee;
The Secretary of the Environment or the Secretary's designee;
A hydrogeologist;
At least two individuals from the bottled water processing industry;
At least one individual from the bottled water distribution industry;
At least one individual from the environmental community or consumer advocacy community; and
At least one consumer of bottled water.
